def feature_sel_mod(df):

    feature_list1=[]
    #feature_list2=[]
    col_list=list(df.columns)
    #print(col_list)
    col_list.remove('ST')
    col_list.remove('STRAIN')

    # Select genes >40% in atleast one ST
    for i in col_list:
        #print(i)
        gene=df[i]
        st=df['ST']
        df_test= pd.concat([gene, st], axis=1)
        df1=list(df_test.groupby(by=['ST'])[i].apply(lambda x: 100*x.sum()/x.count()))
        #print(i,df1)
        counter1=0
        counter2=0
        for j in df1:
        #print(i)
            if(j>40):
                counter1=counter1+1
                
        
        for k in df1:
            if (k<90):
                counter2=counter2+1
        
        #print(df1,i,counter1, counter2)
        if(counter1>0 and counter2>0):
            #print(i)
            feature_list1.append(i)

    feature_list1.append('STRAIN')
    #feature_list1

    #final dataframe
    df_selected=df[feature_list1]
    df_selected.shape

    return(df_selected)

def merge_features(list):
    
    l=list.copy()
    x=l.pop(0)
    x_df=globals()[x]
    for i in l:
        x_df=pd.merge(x_df,globals()[i],how='outer').fillna(0)
    return(x_df)

def draw_roc_auc_plot(y_test, y_pred_proba):
    # roc curve for classes
    fpr = {}
    tpr = {}
    thresh ={}
    roc_auc = dict()
    n_class = 19


    for i in range(n_class):
        fpr[i], tpr[i], thresh[i] = roc_curve(y_test, y_pred_proba[:,i], pos_label=i)
        roc_auc[i] = auc(fpr[i], tpr[i])
    
    colors = cycle(['blue', 'red', 'green'])

    for i, color in zip(range(n_class), colors):
        plt.plot(fpr[i], tpr[i], color=color, lw=1.5, label='ROC curve of class {0} (area = {1:0.2f})' ''.format(i+1, roc_auc[i]))

    plt.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k-', lw=1.5)
    plt.xlim([-0.05, 1.0])
    plt.ylim([0.0, 1.05])
    plt.xlabel('False Positive Rate')
    plt.ylabel('True Positive Rate')
    plt.title('Receiver operating characteristic for multi-class data')
    plt.legend(loc="lower right")
    plt.show()

def run_classifiers(x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test):
    
    # defining a list of classfication algorithms to be considered for ensemble
    random_state = 10
    # KNN
    KNN  = KNeighborsClassifier()

    #logistic regression
    #LOG=LogisticRegression(random_state = random_state)
    #SVC
    #SV=SVC(random_state=random_state)

    #Naive Bayes
    CB = CategoricalNB()

    #Decision Trees
    #DT=DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=random_state)
    
    #Random Forests
    RF=RandomForestClassifier(random_state=randomstate)
    
       
    #ExtrATrees
    et=ExtraTreesClassifier(random_state=random_state)

    #classifiers=[KNN, LOG, SV, NB, DT, RF, gb, et]
    classifiers=[KNN, CB, RF, et]
    

    pf=pd.DataFrame(columns=['Model','Training-accuracy','Testing-accuracy','F1-score', 'recall', 'precision'])

    for i in classifiers:

        name,i_train_score, i_test_score, i_f1, i_r, i_p=run_model(i, x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test)
        pf = pf.append({'Model': name,'Training-accuracy':i_train_score,'Testing-accuracy': i_test_score,'F1-score':i_f1, 'recall':i_r, 'precision':i_p}, ignore_index=True)
        
        
    #XGBoost    
    D_train = xgb.DMatrix(x_train, label=y_train)
    D_test = xgb.DMatrix(x_test, label=y_test)

    param = {
    'eta': 0.3, 
    'max_depth': 3,  
    'objective': 'multi:softmax',  
    'num_class': 19,'nthread': -1} 

    steps = 20  # The number of training iterations

    model = xgb.train(param, D_train, steps)

    preds = model.predict(D_test)
    p=model.predict(D_train)
    best_preds = np.asarray([np.argmax(line) for line in preds])
    best_p = np.asarray([np.argmax(line) for line in p])

    xg_f1=f1_score(y_test, best_preds, average='macro')
    xg_test_score=accuracy_score(y_test, best_preds)
    xg_train_score=accuracy_score(y_train, best_p)
     
    xg_r=recall_score(y_test, best_preds, average='macro')
    xg_p=precision_score(y_test, best_preds, average='macro')
    xg_name=model.__class__.__name__
    pf = pf.append({'Model': 'XGBoost','Training-accuracy':xg_train_score,'Testing-accuracy': xg_test_score,'F1-score':xg_f1,'recall':xg_r, 'precision':xg_p}, ignore_index=True)
   
    #sorting the dataframe according to the testing accuracy
    final_pf = pf.sort_values(by=['Testing-accuracy'], ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)
    
    

    #plotting 

    draw_metrics('Testing-accuracy','Model', final_pf)


    #Plotting the training, testing accuracy scores along with F1 score for each of these models
    #gf=final_pf.copy()
    #gf=gf.set_index('Model')
    #gf=gf.transpose()
    #draw_barplot(gf,gf.columns,3, gf.index)
        
    return(final_pf)

def run_model(clf, x_train, y_train, x_test, y_test):
    '''Self defined function to fit and predict machine learning models'''
    clf.fit(x_train, y_train)
    test_pred=clf.predict(x_test)
    train_pred=clf.predict(x_train)

    
    train_score=accuracy_score(y_train, train_pred)
    test_score=accuracy_score(y_test, test_pred)
    f1=f1_score(y_test, test_pred, average='weighted')
    r=recall_score(y_test, test_pred, average='weighted')
    p=precision_score(y_test, test_pred, average='weighted')
    return clf.__class__.__name__,train_score, test_score, f1, r,p

def hypertune_model(model,params, X_train, X_test ):
    kfold = StratifiedKFold(n_splits=10)
    
        
    #pipe = Pipeline([('m', model)])
    grid = GridSearchCV( model , param_grid = params, cv=kfold, scoring="accuracy", n_jobs= 10, verbose = 1) 
    
    
    %time grid.fit( X_train, y_train) 
    best_model = grid.best_estimator_
    print(" Best cross-validation accuracy: {:.2f}". format( grid.best_score_)) 
    print(" Best parameters: ",grid.best_params_) 
    print(" Train set accuracy: {:.2f}". format( grid.score( X_train, y_train)))
    print(" Test set accuracy: {:.2f}". format( grid.score( X_test, y_test)))
    #important=best_model.feature_importances_

    return(best_model)

def plot_learning_curve(estimator, title, X, y, ylim=None, cv=3,
                        n_jobs=-1, train_sizes=np.linspace(.1, 1.0, 5)):
    """Generate a simple plot of the test and training learning curve"""
    plt.figure(figsize=(8, 6), dpi=300)
    plt.title(title)
    if ylim is not None:
        plt.ylim(*ylim)
    plt.xlabel("Training examples")
    plt.ylabel("Score")
    train_sizes, train_scores, test_scores = learning_curve(
        estimator, X, y, cv=cv, n_jobs=n_jobs, train_sizes=train_sizes)
    train_scores_mean = np.mean(train_scores, axis=1)
    train_scores_std = np.std(train_scores, axis=1)
    test_scores_mean = np.mean(test_scores, axis=1)
    test_scores_std = np.std(test_scores, axis=1)
    plt.grid()

    plt.fill_between(train_sizes, train_scores_mean - train_scores_std,
                     train_scores_mean + train_scores_std, alpha=0.1,
                     color="r")
    plt.fill_between(train_sizes, test_scores_mean - test_scores_std,
                     test_scores_mean + test_scores_std, alpha=0.1, color="g")
    plt.plot(train_sizes, train_scores_mean, 'o-', color="r",
             label="Training score")
    plt.plot(train_sizes, test_scores_mean, 'o-', color="g",
             label="Cross-validation score")

    plt.legend(loc="best")
    rpath='RF_LearningCurve.jpg'
    plt.savefig(rpath,dpi=300)

def run_knn(X_train, X_test):
    #HYper tune KNN
    # HYpertune RF

    KNN  = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=10, weights='distance', metric='jaccard')
 
    KNN.fit(X_train, y_train)
    test_pred=KNN.predict(X_test)
    train_pred=KNN.predict(X_train)
    score=accuracy_score(y_test, test_pred)
    report = classification_report(y_test, test_pred, output_dict=True)
    report_df = pd.DataFrame(report).transpose()
    return(score, report_df)

from sklearn.base import clone

def dropcol_importances(rf, X_train, y_train):
    counter=1
    rf_ = clone(rf)
    rf_.random_state = 17
    rf_.fit(X_train, y_train)
    baseline = rf_.oob_score_
    imp = []
    for col in col_list:
        print(counter,end=',')
        counter=counter+1
        X = X_train.drop(col, axis=1)
        rf_ = clone(rf)
        rf_.random_state = 17
        rf_.fit(X, y_train)
        o = rf_.oob_score_
        imp.append(baseline - o)
    imp = np.array(imp)
    I = pd.DataFrame(
            data={'Feature':col_list,
                  'Importance':imp})
    I = I.set_index('Feature')
    I = I.sort_values('Importance', ascending=True)
    return I

def run_knn(X_train, X_test):
    #HYper tune KNN
    # HYpertune RF

    KNN  = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=10, weights='distance', metric='jaccard')
 
    KNN.fit(X_train, y_train)
    test_pred=KNN.predict(X_test)
    train_pred=KNN.predict(X_train)
    score=accuracy_score(y_test, test_pred)
    report = classification_report(y_test, test_pred, output_dict=True)
    report_df = pd.DataFrame(report).transpose()
    return(score, report_df)
